HEADWORD: Joinery
<hw>Join"er*y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The art, or trade,
of a joiner; the work of a joiner; doing the woodwork (as doors, stairs,
etc.) necessary for the finishing of buildings.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A piece of <qex>joinery</qex> . . . whimsically dovetailed.</q>
<rj><qau>Burke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Joinhand</ent>⟦br⟧
